    <subfield code="a">Mrs. Mary Merrick Brooks hopes that Wendell Phillips will come to Concord, &quot;as he will draw out more than any other person.&quot; Mary M. Brooks wishes to see Maria Weston Chapman with her husband at the Concord meeting and suggests that Mrs. Chapman &quot;get a large delegation from Boston. Mary M. Brooks comments: &quot;I want Douglass &amp; Collins and in short feel the infiniteness of my nature by wishing the whole universe to be present.&quot;</subfield>
